<h1>Web application development for JSR286 portlet container</h1>
<p>
Rails-portlet runs a webapp, such as Ruby on Rails, in a standard <a href="http://jcp.org/en/jsr/detail?id=286">JSR286 Java portlet</a>. The tools and default configuration have been developed in  <a href="http://www.liferay.com">Liferay</a> &amp; Rails with PostgreSQL (optional). This makes agile portlet development on J2EE platform easier to manage.
</p>
