<h1>FAQ</h1>
<h2>What environment does this run in?</h2>
<p>
Liferay 5.x, tested on Tomcat. Rails 2.x has been used on a number of projects, deployed to production as JRuby servlets and on MRI Mongrel dispatchers.<br />
Regarding application development for the Liferay platform and database integration, the v5 schema modeling is working only on PostgreSQL.
</p>

<h2>So how do I get started?</h2>
<p>
The aim of this project is to get development quickly on track, with as much automation as possible, using Liferay as the CMS and Rails to write custom applications. If you want to build a Rails app and run it in a portlet, start from the <%= link_to 'setup guide', doc_url(:action => 'defaultsetup') %>.
</p>

<h2>What about other portals?</h2>
<p>
Portals without support for portlet filters introduced in the JSR286 spec are not supported.
</p>

<h2>What about other frameworks?</h2>
<p>
If you want to develop, say, a <em>Django</em> app, or a <em>.NET</em> app, nothing is stopping you. You will need to update the portlet XML files manually, but <em>html2jsr286</em> allows you to run arbitrary webapp in a portlet.
</p>

<h2>What about Web Proxy Portlet or portletbridge?</h2>
